{"type":"text","timestamp":1784196705562,"sessionID":"ses_0959a3478ffeuLXrAaMyiLpsZJ","part":{"id":"prt_f6a692d0e001uTZD3o5W3RSf08","messageID":"msg_f6a68fcc1001g6APocf73tlj4R","sessionID":"ses_0959a3478ffeuLXrAaMyiLpsZJ","type":"text","text":"I have strong research data. Let me examine the existing mcp-tooling skill patterns and UTCP config format to ground the contrast/registration findings.","time":{"start":1784196705550,"end":1784196705560}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784196705565,"sessionID":"ses_0959a3478ffeuLXrAaMyiLpsZJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_719042de3a0b49f599d6e08b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-chrome-devtools/SKILL.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-chrome-devtools/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: mcp-chrome-devtools\n3: description: \"Chrome DevTools orchestrator: routes between bdg CLI (fast, token-efficient) and Code Mode MCP (multi-tool integration).\"\n4: allowed-tools: [Bash, Edit, Glob, Grep, mcp__code_mode__call_tool_chain, Read, Write]\n5: version: 1.0.9.0\n6: ---\n7: \n8: <!-- Keywords: chrome-devtools, cdp, browser-debugger-cli, bdg, browser-automation, terminal-debugging, screenshot-capture, network-monitoring, mcp-code-mode, orchestrator -->\n9: \n10: # Chrome DevTools Orchestrator - CLI + MCP Integration\n11: \n12: Browser debugging and automation through two complementary approaches: CLI (bdg) for speed and token efficiency, MCP for multi-tool integration.\n13: \n14: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\n15: \n16: ### Activation Triggers\n17: \n18: **Use when**:\n19: - User mentions \"browser debugging\", \"Chrome DevTools\", \"CDP\" explicitly\n20: - User asks to inspect, test, or automate browser tasks with lightweight CLI approach\n21: - User wants screenshots, HAR files, console logs, or network inspection via terminal\n22: - User mentions \"bdg\" or \"browser-debugger-cli\" explicitly\n23: - User needs quick DOM queries, cookie manipulation, or JavaScript execution in browser\n24: - User wants terminal-based browser automation with Unix pipe composability\n25: - User needs production-ready automation scripts for CI/CD browser testing\n26: \n27: **Automatic Triggers**:\n28: - \"bdg\", \"browser-debugger-cli\" mentioned explicitly\n29: - \"lightweight browser debugging\" or \"quick CDP access\"\n30: - \"terminal-based browser automation\"\n31: - \"screenshot without Puppeteer\"\n32: \n33: ### When NOT to Use\n34: \n35: **Do not use for**:\n36: - Complex UI testing suites requiring sophisticated frameworks (use Puppeteer/Playwright)\n37: - Heavy multi-step automation workflows better suited for frameworks\n38: - Cross-browser testing (bdg supports Chrome/Chromium/Edge only)\n39: - Visual regression testing or complex test frameworks\n40: - When user explicitly requests Puppeteer, Playwright, or Selenium\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n45: \n46: \n47: ### Resource Loading Levels\n48: \n49: | Level       | When to Load             | Resources                       |\n50: | ----------- | ------------------------ | ------------------------------- |\n51: | ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation   | Core CDP pattern reference      |\n52: | CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match  | CLI/MCP/session/troubleshooting |\n53: | ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request | Full diagnostics set            |\n54: \n55: ### Smart Router Pseudocode\n56: \n57: The authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, and ambiguity handling.\n58: \n59: - Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively scans skill-local `references/` and `assets/` when those folders exist.\n60: - Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` uses `_guard_in_skill()`, the discovered `inventory`, and a `seen` set.\n61: - Pattern 3: Simple Intent Routing - CLI/MCP/install/troubleshoot/automation intents select the real flat `references/*.md` resources. This skill currently has no keyed `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` resource subdirectories.\n62: - Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` requests CLI/MCP/session disambiguation, and missing intent routes return a \"no knowledge base\" notice while retaining the default CDP reference when available.\n63: \n64: ```python\n65: from pathlib import Path\n66: \n67: SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n68: RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\n69: DEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/cdp_patterns.md\"\n70: \n71: UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n72:     \"Confirm CLI vs MCP path\",\n73:     \"Confirm target browser/session\",\n74:     \"Provide one error, URL, or task goal\",\n75: ]\n76: \n77: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n78:     \"CLI\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"bdg\", \"browser-debugger-cli\", \"terminal\", \"cli\", \"command line\", \"command-line\", \"shell\", \"headless\", \"lightweight\", \"token efficient\"]},\n79:     \"MCP\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"mcp\", \"code mode\", \"multi-tool\", \"parallel sessions\", \"model context protocol\", \"multiple tools\", \"isolated instances\", \"tool chain\", \"in parallel\"]},\n80:     \"INSTALL\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"install\", \"setup\", \"not installed\", \"command -v bdg\", \"set up\", \"getting started\", \"download\", \"npm install\", \"not found\", \"first time\"]},\n81:     \"TROUBLESHOOT\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"error\", \"failed\", \"troubleshoot\", \"session issue\", \"keeps dropping\", \"won't connect\", \"figure out why\", \"hangs\", \"hanging\", \"stuck\", \"crash\", \"crashing\", \"broken\", \"not working\", \"timeout\", \"disconnect\", \"flaky\", \"root cause\"]},\n82:     \"AUTOMATION\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"ci\", \"pipeline\", \"automation\", \"production\", \"automate\", \"unattended\", \"continuous integration\", \"batch\", \"recurring\"]},\n83: }\n84: \n85: RESOURCE_MAP = {\n86:     \"CLI\": [\"references/cdp_patterns.md\", \"references/session-management.md\"],\n87:     \"MCP\": [\"references/session-management.md\", \"references/cdp_patterns.md\"],\n88:     \"INSTALL\": [\"references/troubleshooting.md\"],\n89:     \"TROUBLESHOOT\": [\"references/troubleshooting.md\"],\n90:     \"AUTOMATION\": [\"references/cdp_patterns.md\", \"references/session-management.md\"],\n91: }\n92: \n93: LOADING_LEVELS = {\n94:     \"ALWAYS\": [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n95:     \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full troubleshooting\", \"full session guide\", \"all patterns\", \"capture a har\", \"console errors\", \"routing dashboard\", \"staging\", \"devtools\"],\n96:     \"ON_DEMAND\": [\"references/troubleshooting.md\", \"references/session-management.md\"],\n97: }\n98: \n99: def _task_text(task) -> str:\n100:     parts = [\n101:         str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")),\n102:         str(getattr(task, \"query\", \"\")),\n103:         \" \".join(getattr(task, \"keywords\", []) or []),\n104:     ]\n105:     return \" \".join(parts).lower()\n106: \n107: def _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n108:     resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n109:     resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n110:     if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n111:         raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n112:     return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n113: \n114: def discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n115:     docs = []\n116:     for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n117:         if base.exists():\n118:             docs.extend(p for p in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if p.is_file())\n119:     return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n120: \n121: def score_intents(task) -> dict[str, float]:\n122:     \"\"\"Weighted intent scoring from request text and routing signals.\"\"\"\n123:     text = _task_text(task)\n124:     scores = {intent: 0.0 for intent in INTENT_SIGNALS}\n125:     for intent, cfg in INTENT_SIGNALS.items():\n126:         for keyword in cfg[\"keywords\"]:\n127:             if keyword in text:\n128:                 scores[intent] += cfg[\"weight\"]\n129:     if getattr(task, \"cli_available\", False):\n130:         scores[\"CLI\"] += 5\n131:     if getattr(task, \"code_mode_configured\", False):\n132:         scores[\"MCP\"] += 4\n133:     if getattr(task, \"has_error\", False):\n134:         scores[\"TROUBLESHOOT\"] += 4\n135:     return scores\n136: \n137: def select_intents(scores: dict[str, float], ambiguity_delta: float = 1.0, max_intents: int = 2) -> list[str]:\n138:     ranked = sorted(scores.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse=True)\n139:     if not ranked or ranked[0][1] <= 0:\n140:         return [\"UNKNOWN\"]\n141:     selected = [ranked[0][0]]\n142:     if len(ranked) > 1 and ranked[1][1] > 0 and (ranked[0][1] - ranked[1][1]) <= ambiguity_delta:\n143:         selected.append(ranked[1][0])\n144:     return selected[:max_intents]\n145: \n146: def route_chrome_devtools_resources(task):\n147:     inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n148:     scores = score_intents(task)\n149:     intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n150:     loaded = []\n151:     seen = set()\n152: \n153:     def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n154:         guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n155:         if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n156:             load(guarded)\n157:             loaded.append(guarded)\n158:             seen.add(guarded)\n159: \n160:     for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n161:         load_if_available(relative_path)\n162: \n163:     if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n164:         return {\n165:             \"routing_key\": \"chrome-devtools\",\n166:             \"intents\": intents,\n167:             \"intent_scores\": scores,\n168:             \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n169:             \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n170:             \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n171:             \"resources\": loaded,\n172:         }\n173: \n174:     matched_intents = []\n175:     for intent in intents:\n176:         before_count = len(loaded)\n177:         for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n178:             load_if_available(relative_path)\n179:         if len(loaded) > before_count:\n180:             matched_intents.append(intent)\n181: \n182:     text = _task_text(task)\n183:     if any(keyword in text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n184:         for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n185:             load_if_available(relative_path)\n186: \n187:     if not loaded:\n188:         load_if_available(DEFAULT_RESOURCE)\n189: \n190:     result = {\"routing_key\": \"chrome-devtools\", \"intents\": intents, \"intent_scores\": scores, \"resources\": loaded}\n191:     if not matched_intents:\n192:         result[\"notice\"] = f\"No knowledge base found for intent(s): {', '.join(intents)}\"\n193:     return result\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n199: \n200: ### Tool Comparison\n201: \n202: Prefer CLI (`bdg`) for fast, low-token browser inspection. Use MCP via Code Mode when browser work must be chained with other tools or parallel isolated sessions.\n203: \n204: ### CLI Approach (Priority) - browser-debugger-cli (bdg)\n205: \n206: #### Installation & Verification\n207: \n208: Check with `command -v bdg`, install with `npm install -g browser-debugger-cli@alpha`, then verify `bdg --version 2>&1`.\n209: \n210: ### MCP Approach (Fallback) - Chrome DevTools via Code Mode\n211: \n212: When CLI unavailable or multi-tool integration needed.\n213: \n214: #### Prerequisites\n215: \n216: 1. Code Mode configured in `.utcp_config.json`\n217: 2. Chrome DevTools MCP server registered with `--isolated=true`\n218: \n219: #### Isolated Instances\n220: \n221: **Key Feature**: MCP uses `--isolated=true` flag for independent browser instances.\n222: \n223: **Benefits of isolated instances:**\n224: - Each instance runs in its own browser process\n225: - Multiple parallel browser sessions possible\n226: - No session conflicts between instances\n227: - Register multiple instances for parallel testing (e.g., `chrome_devtools_1`, `chrome_devtools_2`)\n228: \n229: Configure one or more Chrome DevTools MCP entries in `.utcp_config.json` with `--isolated=true` when parallel browser sessions are needed.\n230: \n231: #### Configuration Check\n232: \n233: ```bash\n234: cat .utcp_config.json | jq '.manual_call_templates[] | select(.name | startswith(\"chrome_devtools\"))'\n235: ```\n236: \n237: #### Invocation Pattern\n238: \n239: Tool naming is `{manual_name}.{manual_name}_{tool_name}`. Run MCP browser operations inside `call_tool_chain()` and close pages in a `finally` block.\n240: \n241: #### Available MCP Tools\n242: \n243: Common MCP tools include navigation, screenshots, console messages, viewport resize, clicks, form fill, hover, keyboard, waits, page creation/selection/close. Use underscores in tool names and confirm exact names with Code Mode discovery.\n244: \n245: #### When to Prefer MCP\n246: \n247: - Already using Code Mode for other tools (external services, Figma, etc.)\n248: - Need to chain browser operations with other MCP tools\n249: - **Parallel browser testing** - compare multiple sites/viewports simultaneously\n250: - Complex multi-step automation in TypeScript\n251: - Type-safe tool invocation required\n252: \n253: #### MCP Limitations\n254: \n255: - Higher token cost than CLI\n256: - Requires Code Mode infrastructure\n257: - Subset of CDP methods (CLI has 300+ methods across 53 domains)\n258: - Less self-documenting than CLI's `--list`, `--describe`\n259: \n260: ### MCP Session Cleanup\n261: \n262: Always close browser instances when done. Wrap Code Mode browser operations in `try/finally` so cleanup runs even on errors.\n263: \n264: ---\n265: \n266: ## 4. RULES\n267: \n268: ### ✅ ALWAYS Rules\n269: \n270: 1. Check CLI availability first and prefer CLI when it fits.\n271: 2. Use discovery commands before CDP methods.\n272: 3. Verify session status before CDP commands.\n273: 4. Capture stderr with `2>&1`.\n274: 5. Stop sessions after operations.\n275: 6. Use `jq` for JSON processing.\n276: \n277: ### ⛔ NEVER Rules\n278: \n279: 1. Execute CDP commands without an active session.\n280: 2. Hardcode CDP method lists.\n281: 3. Skip error handling or exit-code checks.\n282: 4. Leave sessions running.\n283: 5. Assume method names without discovery.\n284: 6. Use on Windows without WSL.\n285: \n286: ### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n287: \n288: 1. Chrome/Chromium cannot be found.\n289: 2. Sessions fail after 3 retries.\n290: 3. Cross-browser testing is required.\n291: 4. Complex UI testing needs a heavier framework.\n292: 5. Windows use lacks WSL.\n293: \n294: ---\n295: \n296: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n297: \n298: ### Browser Debugging Completion Checklist\n299: \n300: Workflow is complete when CLI/MCP path is selected, installation or config is verified, session is active, CDP operations exit 0 with valid JSON, requested data is captured, sessions are cleaned up, and discovery/error handling are documented.\n301: \n302: ### Quality Targets\n303: \n304: Quality targets are fast session startup, quick screenshot/console capture, and handled errors.\n305: \n306: ---\n307: \n308: ## 6. INTEGRATION POINTS\n309: \n310: ### Framework Integration\n311: \n312: This skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in [AGENTS.md](../../../../AGENTS.md).\n313: \n314: Key integrations:\n315: - **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py`\n316: - **Tool Routing**: Per AGENTS.md Section 6 decision tree\n317: - **Memory**: Context preserved via Spec Kit Memory MCP\n318: \n319: ### Tool Usage Guidelines\n320: \n321: Use Bash for `bdg`, Read for references, Grep for logs/output, and Glob for screenshots/HAR exports. Chrome/Chromium is the runtime; set `CHROME_PATH` if auto-detection fails.\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ## 7. QUICK REFERENCE\n326: \n327: ### Essential CLI Commands\n328: \n329: Use `bdg cdp --list`, `bdg cdp --describe <domain>`, `bdg cdp --search <term>`, `bdg <url>`, `bdg status`, `bdg stop`, `bdg dom screenshot <path>`, `bdg console --list`, `bdg dom query`, `bdg dom eval`, and `bdg network har <path>`. In shell scripts, install a trap so `bdg stop 2>&1` runs on exit.\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n334: \n335: The router discovers markdown resources dynamically from `references/` and `assets/` when those directories exist. This skill currently routes over the flat reference set: `references/cdp_patterns.md`, `references/session-management.md`, and `references/troubleshooting.md`.\n336: \n337: Scripts: `scripts/install.sh`.\n338: \n339: Examples: [`examples/README.md`](examples/README.md) — automation example scripts. It lives outside the `references/`/`assets/` discovery roots, so it is linked here rather than auto-loaded by the router.\n340: \n341: Related skills: `mcp-code-mode` for MCP fallback and `sk-code` for browser verification in application-code workflows.\n342: \n343: Install guide: [INSTALL_GUIDE.md](INSTALL_GUIDE.md).\n\n(End of file - total 343 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: mcp-chrome-devtools\ndescription: \"Chrome DevTools orchestrator: routes between bdg CLI (fast, token-efficient) and Code Mode MCP (multi-tool integration).\"\nallowed-tools: [Bash, Edit, Glob, Grep, mcp__code_mode__call_tool_chain, Read, Write]\nversion: 1.0.9.0\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: chrome-devtools, cdp, browser-debugger-cli, bdg, browser-automation, terminal-debugging, screenshot-capture, network-monitoring, mcp-code-mode, orchestrator -->\n\n# Chrome DevTools Orchestrator - CLI + MCP Integration\n\nBrowser debugging and automation through two complementary approaches: CLI (bdg) for speed and token efficiency, MCP for multi-tool integration.\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### Activation Triggers\n\n**Use when**:\n- User mentions \"browser debugging\", \"Chrome DevTools\", \"CDP\" explicitly\n- User asks to inspect, test, or automate browser tasks with lightweight CLI approach","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-chrome-devtools/SKILL.md","text":"---\nname: mcp-chrome-devtools\ndescription: \"Chrome DevTools orchestrator: routes between bdg CLI (fast, token-efficient) and Code Mode MCP (multi-tool integration).\"\nallowed-tools: [Bash, Edit, Glob, Grep, mcp__code_mode__call_tool_chain, Read, Write]\nversion: 1.0.9.0\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: chrome-devtools, cdp, browser-debugger-cli, bdg, browser-automation, terminal-debugging, screenshot-capture, network-monitoring, mcp-code-mode, orchestrator -->\n\n# Chrome DevTools Orchestrator - CLI + MCP Integration\n\nBrowser debugging and automation through two complementary approaches: CLI (bdg) for speed and token efficiency, MCP for multi-tool integration.\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### Activation Triggers\n\n**Use when**:\n- User mentions \"browser debugging\", \"Chrome DevTools\", \"CDP\" explicitly\n- User asks to inspect, test, or automate browser tasks with lightweight CLI approach\n- User wants screenshots, HAR files, console logs, or network inspection via terminal\n- User mentions \"bdg\" or \"browser-debugger-cli\" explicitly\n- User needs quick DOM queries, cookie manipulation, or JavaScript execution in browser\n- User wants terminal-based browser automation with Unix pipe composability\n- User needs production-ready automation scripts for CI/CD browser testing\n\n**Automatic Triggers**:\n- \"bdg\", \"browser-debugger-cli\" mentioned explicitly\n- \"lightweight browser debugging\" or \"quick CDP access\"\n- \"terminal-based browser automation\"\n- \"screenshot without Puppeteer\"\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n**Do not use for**:\n- Complex UI testing suites requiring sophisticated frameworks (use Puppeteer/Playwright)\n- Heavy multi-step automation workflows better suited for frameworks\n- Cross-browser testing (bdg supports Chrome/Chromium/Edge only)\n- Visual regression testing or complex test frameworks\n- When user explicitly requests Puppeteer, Playwright, or Selenium\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level       | When to Load             | Resources                       |\n| ----------- | ------------------------ | ------------------------------- |\n| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation   | Core CDP pattern reference      |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match  | CLI/MCP/session/troubleshooting |\n| ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request | Full diagnostics set            |\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\nThe authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, and ambiguity handling.\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively scans skill-local `references/` and `assets/` when those folders exist.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` uses `_guard_in_skill()`, the discovered `inventory`, and a `seen` set.\n- Pattern 3: Simple Intent Routing - CLI/MCP/install/troubleshoot/automation intents select the real flat `references/*.md` resources. This skill currently has no keyed `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` resource subdirectories.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` requests CLI/MCP/session disambiguation, and missing intent routes return a \"no knowledge base\" notice while retaining the default CDP reference when available.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/cdp_patterns.md\"\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm CLI vs MCP path\",\n    \"Confirm target browser/session\",\n    \"Provide one error, URL, or task goal\",\n]\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"CLI\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"bdg\", \"browser-debugger-cli\", \"terminal\", \"cli\", \"command line\", \"command-line\", \"shell\", \"headless\", \"lightweight\", \"token efficient\"]},\n    \"MCP\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"mcp\", \"code mode\", \"multi-tool\", \"parallel sessions\", \"model context protocol\", \"multiple tools\", \"isolated instances\", \"tool chain\", \"in parallel\"]},\n    \"INSTALL\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"install\", \"setup\", \"not installed\", \"command -v bdg\", \"set up\", \"getting started\", \"download\", \"npm install\", \"not found\", \"first time\"]},\n    \"TROUBLESHOOT\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"error\", \"failed\", \"troubleshoot\", \"session issue\", \"keeps dropping\", \"won't connect\", \"figure out why\", \"hangs\", \"hanging\", \"stuck\", \"crash\", \"crashing\", \"broken\", \"not working\", \"timeout\", \"disconnect\", \"flaky\", \"root cause\"]},\n    \"AUTOMATION\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"ci\", \"pipeline\", \"automation\", \"production\", \"automate\", \"unattended\", \"continuous integration\", \"batch\", \"recurring\"]},\n}\n\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"CLI\": [\"references/cdp_patterns.md\", \"references/session-management.md\"],\n    \"MCP\": [\"references/session-management.md\", \"references/cdp_patterns.md\"],\n    \"INSTALL\": [\"references/troubleshooting.md\"],\n    \"TROUBLESHOOT\": [\"references/troubleshooting.md\"],\n    \"AUTOMATION\": [\"references/cdp_patterns.md\", \"references/session-management.md\"],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\": [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full troubleshooting\", \"full session guide\", \"all patterns\", \"capture a har\", \"console errors\", \"routing dashboard\", \"staging\", \"devtools\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\": [\"references/troubleshooting.md\", \"references/session-management.md\"],\n}\n\ndef _task_text(task) -> str:\n    parts = [\n        str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")),\n        str(getattr(task, \"query\", \"\")),\n        \" \".join(getattr(task, \"keywords\", []) or []),\n    ]\n    return \" \".join(parts).lower()\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(p for p in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if p.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n\ndef score_intents(task) -> dict[str, float]:\n    \"\"\"Weighted intent scoring from request text and routing signals.\"\"\"\n    text = _task_text(task)\n    scores = {intent: 0.0 for intent in INTENT_SIGNALS}\n    for intent, cfg in INTENT_SIGNALS.items():\n        for keyword in cfg[\"keywords\"]:\n            if keyword in text:\n                scores[intent] += cfg[\"weight\"]\n    if getattr(task, \"cli_available\", False):\n        scores[\"CLI\"] += 5\n    if getattr(task, \"code_mode_configured\", False):\n        scores[\"MCP\"] += 4\n    if getattr(task, \"has_error\", False):\n        scores[\"TROUBLESHOOT\"] += 4\n    return scores\n\ndef select_intents(scores: dict[str, float], ambiguity_delta: float = 1.0, max_intents: int = 2) -> list[str]:\n    ranked = sorted(scores.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse=True)\n    if not ranked or ranked[0][1] <= 0:\n        return [\"UNKNOWN\"]\n    selected = [ranked[0][0]]\n    if len(ranked) > 1 and ranked[1][1] > 0 and (ranked[0][1] - ranked[1][1]) <= ambiguity_delta:\n        selected.append(ranked[1][0])\n    return selected[:max_intents]\n\ndef route_chrome_devtools_resources(task):\n    inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n    scores = score_intents(task)\n    intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n    loaded = []\n    seen = set()\n\n    def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n        guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n        if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n            load(guarded)\n            loaded.append(guarded)\n            seen.add(guarded)\n\n    for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n        return {\n            \"routing_key\": \"chrome-devtools\",\n            \"intents\": intents,\n            \"intent_scores\": scores,\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    matched_intents = []\n    for intent in intents:\n        before_count = len(loaded)\n        for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n        if len(loaded) > before_count:\n            matched_intents.append(intent)\n\n    text = _task_text(task)\n    if any(keyword in text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n        for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    if not loaded:\n        load_if_available(DEFAULT_RESOURCE)\n\n    result = {\"routing_key\": \"chrome-devtools\", \"intents\": intents, \"intent_scores\": scores, \"resources\": loaded}\n    if not matched_intents:\n        result[\"notice\"] = f\"No knowledge base found for intent(s): {', '.join(intents)}\"\n    return result\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Tool Comparison\n\nPrefer CLI (`bdg`) for fast, low-token browser inspection. Use MCP via Code Mode when browser work must be chained with other tools or parallel isolated sessions.\n\n### CLI Approach (Priority) - browser-debugger-cli (bdg)\n\n#### Installation & Verification\n\nCheck with `command -v bdg`, install with `npm install -g browser-debugger-cli@alpha`, then verify `bdg --version 2>&1`.\n\n### MCP Approach (Fallback) - Chrome DevTools via Code Mode\n\nWhen CLI unavailable or multi-tool integration needed.\n\n#### Prerequisites\n\n1. Code Mode configured in `.utcp_config.json`\n2. Chrome DevTools MCP server registered with `--isolated=true`\n\n#### Isolated Instances\n\n**Key Feature**: MCP uses `--isolated=true` flag for independent browser instances.\n\n**Benefits of isolated instances:**\n- Each instance runs in its own browser process\n- Multiple parallel browser sessions possible\n- No session conflicts between instances\n- Register multiple instances for parallel testing (e.g., `chrome_devtools_1`, `chrome_devtools_2`)\n\nConfigure one or more Chrome DevTools MCP entries in `.utcp_config.json` with `--isolated=true` when parallel browser sessions are needed.\n\n#### Configuration Check\n\n```bash\ncat .utcp_config.json | jq '.manual_call_templates[] | select(.name | startswith(\"chrome_devtools\"))'\n```\n\n#### Invocation Pattern\n\nTool naming is `{manual_name}.{manual_name}_{tool_name}`. Run MCP browser operations inside `call_tool_chain()` and close pages in a `finally` block.\n\n#### Available MCP Tools\n\nCommon MCP tools include navigation, screenshots, console messages, viewport resize, clicks, form fill, hover, keyboard, waits, page creation/selection/close. Use underscores in tool names and confirm exact names with Code Mode discovery.\n\n#### When to Prefer MCP\n\n- Already using Code Mode for other tools (external services, Figma, etc.)\n- Need to chain browser operations with other MCP tools\n- **Parallel browser testing** - compare multiple sites/viewports simultaneously\n- Complex multi-step automation in TypeScript\n- Type-safe tool invocation required\n\n#### MCP Limitations\n\n- Higher token cost than CLI\n- Requires Code Mode infrastructure\n- Subset of CDP methods (CLI has 300+ methods across 53 domains)\n- Less self-documenting than CLI's `--list`, `--describe`\n\n### MCP Session Cleanup\n\nAlways close browser instances when done. Wrap Code Mode browser operations in `try/finally` so cleanup runs even on errors.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ✅ ALWAYS Rules\n\n1. Check CLI availability first and prefer CLI when it fits.\n2. Use discovery commands before CDP methods.\n3. Verify session status before CDP commands.\n4. Capture stderr with `2>&1`.\n5. Stop sessions after operations.\n6. Use `jq` for JSON processing.\n\n### ⛔ NEVER Rules\n\n1. Execute CDP commands without an active session.\n2. Hardcode CDP method lists.\n3. Skip error handling or exit-code checks.\n4. Leave sessions running.\n5. Assume method names without discovery.\n6. Use on Windows without WSL.\n\n### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n\n1. Chrome/Chromium cannot be found.\n2. Sessions fail after 3 retries.\n3. Cross-browser testing is required.\n4. Complex UI testing needs a heavier framework.\n5. Windows use lacks WSL.\n\n---\n\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Browser Debugging Completion Checklist\n\nWorkflow is complete when CLI/MCP path is selected, installation or config is verified, session is active, CDP operations exit 0 with valid JSON, requested data is captured, sessions are cleaned up, and discovery/error handling are documented.\n\n### Quality Targets\n\nQuality targets are fast session startup, quick screenshot/console capture, and handled errors.\n\n---\n\n## 6. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in [AGENTS.md](../../../../AGENTS.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py`\n- **Tool Routing**: Per AGENTS.md Section 6 decision tree\n- **Memory**: Context preserved via Spec Kit Memory MCP\n\n### Tool Usage Guidelines\n\nUse Bash for `bdg`, Read for references, Grep for logs/output, and Glob for screenshots/HAR exports. Chrome/Chromium is the runtime; set `CHROME_PATH` if auto-detection fails.\n\n---\n\n## 7. QUICK REFERENCE\n\n### Essential CLI Commands\n\nUse `bdg cdp --list`, `bdg cdp --describe <domain>`, `bdg cdp --search <term>`, `bdg <url>`, `bdg status`, `bdg stop`, `bdg dom screenshot <path>`, `bdg console --list`, `bdg dom query`, `bdg dom eval`, and `bdg network har <path>`. In shell scripts, install a trap so `bdg stop 2>&1` runs on exit.\n\n---\n\n## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router discovers markdown resources dynamically from `references/` and `assets/` when those directories exist. This skill currently routes over the flat reference set: `references/cdp_patterns.md`, `references/session-management.md`, and `references/troubleshooting.md`.\n\nScripts: `scripts/install.sh`.\n\nExamples: [`examples/README.md`](examples/README.md) — automation example scripts. It lives outside the `references/`/`assets/` discovery roots, so it is linked here rather than auto-loaded by the router.\n\nRelated skills: `mcp-code-mode` for MCP fallback and `sk-code` for browser verification in application-code workflows.\n\nInstall guide: [INSTALL_GUIDE.md](INSTALL_GUIDE.md).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":343,"totalLines":343,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-chrome-devtools/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1784196705556,"end":1784196705563}},"id":"prt_f6a692d11001rNdMxipEqqzCqD","sessionID":"ses_0959a3478ffeuLXrAaMyiLpsZJ","messageID":"msg_f6a68fcc1001g6APocf73tlj4R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784196705567,"sessionID":"ses_0959a3478ffeuLXrAaMyiLpsZJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_64f7dbd91fde41dc87c5df52","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.utcp_config.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.utcp_config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"load_variables_from\": [\n3:     {\n4:       \"variable_loader_type\": \"dotenv\",\n5:       \"env_file_path\": \".env\"\n6:     }\n7:   ],\n8:   \"tool_repository\": {\n9:     \"tool_repository_type\": \"in_memory\"\n10:   },\n11:   \"tool_search_strategy\": {\n12:     \"tool_search_strategy_type\": \"tag_and_description_word_match\"\n13:   },\n14:   \"manual_call_templates\": [\n15:     {\n16:       \"name\": \"chrome_devtools_1\",\n17:       \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n18:       \"config\": {\n19:         \"mcpServers\": {\n20:           \"chrome_devtools_1\": {\n21:             \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n22:             \"command\": \"npx\",\n23:             \"args\": [\n24:               \"chrome-devtools-mcp@0.26.0\",\n25:               \"--isolated=true\"\n26:             ],\n27:             \"env\": {}\n28:           }\n29:         }\n30:       }\n31:     },\n32:     {\n33:       \"name\": \"chrome_devtools_2\",\n34:       \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n35:       \"config\": {\n36:         \"mcpServers\": {\n37:           \"chrome_devtools_2\": {\n38:             \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n39:             \"command\": \"npx\",\n40:             \"args\": [\n41:               \"chrome-devtools-mcp@0.26.0\",\n42:               \"--isolated=true\"\n43:             ],\n44:             \"env\": {}\n45:           }\n46:         }\n47:       }\n48:     },\n49:     {\n50:       \"name\": \"clickup_official\",\n51:       \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n52:       \"config\": {\n53:         \"mcpServers\": {\n54:           \"clickup_official\": {\n55:             \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n56:             \"command\": \"npx\",\n57:             \"args\": [\n58:               \"-y\",\n59:               \"@clickup/mcp-server\"\n60:             ],\n61:             \"env\": {\n62:               \"CLICKUP_API_KEY\": \"${CLICKUP_API_KEY}\",\n63:               \"CLICKUP_TEAM_ID\": \"${CLICKUP_TEAM_ID}\"\n64:             }\n65:           }\n66:         }\n67:       }\n68:     },\n69:     {\n70:       \"name\": \"figma\",\n71:       \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n72:       \"config\": {\n73:         \"mcpServers\": {\n74:           \"figma\": {\n75:             \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n76:             \"command\": \"npx\",\n77:             \"args\": [\n78:               \"-y\",\n79:               \"figma-developer-mcp@latest\",\n80:               \"--stdio\"\n81:             ],\n82:             \"env\": {\n83:               \"FIGMA_API_KEY\": \"${FIGMA_API_KEY}\"\n84:             }\n85:           }\n86:         }\n87:       }\n88:     },\n89:     {\n90:       \"name\": \"github\",\n91:       \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n92:       \"config\": {\n93:         \"mcpServers\": {\n94:           \"github\": {\n95:             \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n96:             \"command\": \"npx\",\n97:             \"args\": [\n98:               \"-y\",\n99:               \"@modelcontextprotocol/server-github@latest\"\n100:             ],\n101:             \"env\": {\n102:               \"GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN\": \"${GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN}\"\n103:             }\n104:           }\n105:         }\n106:       }\n107:     },\n108:     {\n109:       \"name\": \"gitkraken\",\n110:       \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n111:       \"config\": {\n112:         \"mcpServers\": {\n113:           \"gitkraken\": {\n114:             \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n115:             \"command\": \"npx\",\n116:             \"args\": [\n117:               \"-y\",\n118:               \"@gitkraken/g